    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 14 June 1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>Lucretia Caballis will tell him what they have heard about the Turks. All
                            of Syria, Egypt, and Greece is trembling with fear. If it is true that
                            the Emperor has defeated Hayreddin Barbarossa Pasha and conquered Tunis,
                            he will focus all his might on these locations. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Idem Nicolao Olao suo salutem.</p>
                <p>Quae a Turcis, <persName>Aenobarbo</persName><note type="critic"
                        >Hayreddin Barbarossa Pasha.</note> et caesaris classe habemus, de
                        <persName>Lucretia Virgine</persName><note type="critic">Lucretia Caballis
                        (vom Ross).</note> electissima intelliges, nos id audivimus
                        <placeName>Syriam</placeName>, <placeName>Aegiptum</placeName> et
                        <placeName>Graeciam</placeName> fere omnem tremere. Quod si verum est,
                    debellato <persName>Aenobarbo</persName> et capto
                        <placeName>Tuneto</placeName><note type="critic">Tunis.</note>
                    <persName>caesar</persName> vires suas in eas partes convertet, et omnia in suam
                    potestatem brevi redacturus est, quod postea succedit, curabo, ut scias. Tu vero
                    interea valebis et <persName>Sceperum</persName><note type="critic">Cornelis de
                        Schepper.</note> nostrum et eius <persName>coniugem</persName><note
                        type="critic">Anna Isabella (Elizabeth) Donche.</note> meo nomine salutabis.
                    Iterum vale, Amicorum Optime. </p>
                <p><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> XIIII. Iunii MDXXXV.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
